### SECTION 4 — DATABASE ARCHITECTURE
The system targets PostgreSQL managed via Drizzle.
Canonical 16 database tables must be defined in `lib/db/schema.ts`:
1. **conversations**: Session container (id, title, personaId, modeId, timestamps).
2. **messages**: Individual chats (id, conversationId, role, content, attachments, provider, timestamp).
3. **memories**: Core preference configurations (id, key, value, category, importance).
4. **notes**: Notepad items (id, title, content, timestamp).
5. **tasks**: To-do items (id, title, notes, priority, dueAt, status, completed).
6. **reminders**: Temporal notification gates (id, title, remindAt, repeat, status).
7. **workflows**: Prompts sequencing plans (id, title, steps).
8. **activity**: Global system log audited actions (id, kind, title, details, timestamp).
9. **settings**: Global preferences (id, language, activeProvider, autonomyLevel, wakeWord, etc.).
10. **agents**: Registered local-PC companion info (id, platform, capabilities, lastSeenAt).
11. **agentActions**: History logs of PC controller executions (id, agentId, kind, payload, result, status).
12. **plans**: Execution steps sequence (id, goal, plan [JSON], status, runtime).
13. **updates**: System updates log (id, manifest [JSON], status, log).
14. **earningProjects**: Client project container (id, name, budget, status).
15. **earningDeliverables**: Milestones tied to projects (id, projectId, title, level, status).
16. **chatInteractions**: Auditable analytics metric tracker (id, provider, model, tokens, latency).

